Description: Fits joint species distribution models (JSDMs) to
    environmental DNA (eDNA) metabarcoding reads data within a hierarchical
    Bayesian occupancy framework. Explicitly models the two-stage
    detection process of field sample collection followed by PCR
    amplification and sequencing, while accounting for species traits,
    residual between-species correlations, and optional spatial
    autocorrelation via a Gaussian process. Models are fit by Markov chain
    Monte Carlo. See Ji et al. (2025) <doi:10.1111/ele.70302> for
    methodological details.
